  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "Poland gained-- regained independence after the First World War.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And-- he was actually well-disposed towards the Jews, so Piłsudski was considered wonderful to the Jews.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "After-- but it must have been quite a bit of anti-Semitism, anyway.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And then later on, when you come to learn world history, and the world, after the-- after we left Poland you find out that Piłsudski was a-- was a dictator.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "He was.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "But then after he died, and there were I mean, there was always several anti-Semitic parties.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE], party, and there was this other.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "I mean, there's-- this was a peasants' party.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "There were always very-- there were always anti-Semites, because [INAUDIBLE] the Jews, I mean, historically-- I'm not going to go through all this Polish history, but historically, of course, the Jews couldn't even-- or very few could even buy land and settle on the land.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "So when they were brought into Poland by this one Polish king in the fourteenth century-- 1348 or something-- they were bringing-- they were brought in an order to sort of establish towns, become tax collectors, become money lenders, because every king was constantly fighting wars or some other duels with some other kings.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So their position was immediately such that the Poles where-- I mean, it was already a country, and it was at that time a feudal-- feudal system-- and the Jews became the ones who were selling them things.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were appointed by the kings, or by those other [INAUDIBLE] or by the other dukes or by other aristocracy, the-- the tax collectors for them.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
